# Ministerial Code Complaint: Lisa Nandy Breaches

## Journey Flowchart

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  A[Complaint to PM Starmer<br/>cc MP<br/>20 Oct 2025 events] --> B{PM assesses referral}
  B -->|Refer Yes| C[Independent Adviser investigates<br/>Code breaches 1.1/2.4/3/2.1]
  B -->|No/Fail| D[Individual escalations]
  C --> E{Breach found?}
  E -->|Yes Success| F[PM sanctions<br/>Apology/remedy/resignation]
  E -->|No Fail| G[Close primary path]
  F --> H[Monitor + optional next]
  D --> I[Optional Advisory<br/>Standards Committee<br/>Individual submit gov.uk]
  D --> J[Private prosecution<br/>CPS Perjury/Misconduct<br/>Solicitor/evidence]
  D --> K[International<br/>UN Rapporteur/ECtHR/ICC]
  G --> I
  G --> J
  G --> K
  H --> I
  H --> L[Media/MP loopback<br/>Pressure PM revisit]
  I --> M{Action?}
  M -->|Yes| N[Oversight forces change]
  M -->|No| O[Escalate further]
  J --> P{CPS Yes?}
  P -->|Yes| Q[Court conviction]
  P -->|No| O
  K --> R{Admissible?}
  R -->|Yes| S[International judgment]
  R -->|No| O
  N --> L
  Q --> H
  S --> H
  O --> H
